        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 7:04PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of Broome, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling City, Broome, Water Valley, and Us-87 Near The Coke-
Tom Green County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
